WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.240 --> 00:00:02.340
- How effective is it training

00:00:02.340 --> 00:00:05.220
with rubber bands to build strength?

00:00:06.090 --> 00:00:09.360
The answer is not effective at all.

00:00:09.360 --> 00:00:11.070
I know some of you're gonna be surprised

00:00:11.070 --> 00:00:12.990
that I'm saying something like that.

00:00:12.990 --> 00:00:17.190
Bands buy themselves are trash.

00:00:17.190 --> 00:00:19.170
You can't really do anything with them.

00:00:19.170 --> 00:00:21.660
They're gonna twist your
joints, they're gonna hurt you.

00:00:21.660 --> 00:00:24.360
And probably the most important thing

00:00:24.360 --> 00:00:26.010
that you're missing when
you're training with bands

00:00:26.010 --> 00:00:29.700
by themselves is you're
not loading the bottom.

00:00:29.700 --> 00:00:31.740
You have to load the bottom.

00:00:31.740 --> 00:00:34.350
That's where the stimulus
happens, the stretch position,

00:00:34.350 --> 00:00:36.090
the all the way back position.

00:00:36.090 --> 00:00:39.000
You need to have some force there

00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:41.700
because ultimately, as you do repetitions,

00:00:41.700 --> 00:00:44.220
let's say I'm doing 20
repetitions on chest press,

00:00:44.220 --> 00:00:47.820
I'm gonna get to the point
where I shorten the repetitions

00:00:47.820 --> 00:00:51.000
because I'm losing access to the muscle.

00:00:51.000 --> 00:00:53.760
And a lot of the cells are
basically disqualifying

00:00:53.760 --> 00:00:55.560
themselves from being
part of the contraction

00:00:55.560 --> 00:00:57.000
because they've been exhausted.

00:00:57.000 --> 00:01:01.560
So with variable resistance,
now this is a band plus a bar

00:01:01.560 --> 00:01:04.590
that keeps my wrist straight.

00:01:04.590 --> 00:01:07.380
So I'm pushing as many times as I can.

00:01:07.380 --> 00:01:10.440
Now, I can go to fatigue
in diminishing range.

00:01:10.440 --> 00:01:13.410
So I might get in, in my first set,

00:01:13.410 --> 00:01:17.190
I might get five fatigue
points in one set.

00:01:17.190 --> 00:01:20.340
So that gives me potentially, like,

00:01:20.340 --> 00:01:23.790
this has been marginally proven in Dr.

00:01:23.790 --> 00:01:25.560
Sean Conley's research,

00:01:25.560 --> 00:01:30.560
but you get sort of five
times the stimulus in one set

00:01:30.570 --> 00:01:33.360
that you would normally get
with a, with a weight set.

00:01:33.360 --> 00:01:36.360
But that doesn't apply to bands.

00:01:36.360 --> 00:01:40.170
It's because there's an
apparatus attached to the band so

00:01:40.170 --> 00:01:42.360
that you can really load the bottom

00:01:42.360 --> 00:01:45.480
and get full access to the
power that the band has.

00:01:45.480 --> 00:01:50.430
So when somebody says you can
either do great with bands

00:01:50.430 --> 00:01:52.110
or you can't do great with bands,

00:01:52.110 --> 00:01:54.510
there's a, it's not that simple.

00:01:54.510 --> 00:01:57.930
It's are you using bands
as a part of a strategy

00:01:57.930 --> 00:02:01.080
to load the entire full range of motion?

00:02:01.080 --> 00:02:04.740
If yes, then you can do phenomenal.

00:02:04.740 --> 00:02:09.000
But that's not really the
question When someone says bands,

00:02:09.000 --> 00:02:10.260
bands suck.

